header.gameNote: SOUTH PADRE ISLAND INVITATIONAL AT SOUTH PADRE ISLAND TX

article.headline: Austin Peay 57, Delaware State 51
article.story: SOUTH PADRE ISLAND, Texas (AP) -- Maurice Hampton scored 18 points and Zac Schlader added 15, including the go-ahead score with 2:14 remaining, as Austin Peay beat Delaware State 57-51 Friday in the South Padre Island Invitational. Schlader's layup gave Austin Peay (1-3) its first lead of the game at 50-48 and the Governors never trailed after that. Schlader also had eight rebounds. Delaware State (1-3) led 22-17 and halftime and went up 43-33 before Austin Peay came back with a 19-5 run. Landon Shipley tied the score at 46 with a pair of free throws, and Hampton tied it again at 48 with a layup before Schlader's shot. Jahsha Bluntt led Delaware State with 11 points and nine rebounds.
